The paper deals with the problem of counting induced subgraphs with certain properties, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem is shown to be #W[1]-hard, which is a complexity class related to parameterized complexity (cs.CC). The authors use a topological approach and a framework of graph motif parameters, which are techniques commonly used in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also involves algebraic techniques, which are often used in graph theory and combinatorics (cs.GT).
